  "id": "BIT-discourse-2026-44785",
  "summary": "Discourse: Hidden reply-to post raw can be disclosed through AI explain prompts",
  "details": "Discourse is an open-source discussion platform. From versions 2026.1.0 to before 2026.1.4, 2026.3.0 to before 2026.3.1, and 2026.4.0 to before 2026.4.1, the AI \"explain\" helper only checks can_see? on the post being explained, not its reply_to_post, so any authenticated user with access to the AI helper could read the raw contents of a hidden parent post by invoking \"Explain\" on a reply to it. This issue has been patched in versions 2026.1.4, 2026.3.1, 2026.4.1, and 2026.5.0.",
